    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offensive engine is anchored today by **Kyle Tucker** (74.27) and **Drake Baldwin** (71.77), our clear-cut top starts. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a high-floor matchup against Dustin May, where the combination of the #4 lineup spot and wind blowing out at the park provides the necessary boost to reach elite status. Meanwhile, **Drake Baldwin** is elevated significantly by a favorable park factor and a projected turn at the top of the order; his ability to capitalize on Kyle Freeland\u2019s projected 4.27 xERA makes him the preferred choice at C1. **Josh Lowe** also warrants attention with a strong 65.65 score; his dynamic platoon edge against Clay Holmes, combined with his speed profile, makes him a priority start even against a competent arm.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the lineup optimizer today was the benching of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (53.50), who missed the cut despite a respectable projection. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** possesses an impressive 0.386 xwOBA, the combination of Joe Ryan\u2019s 3.39 xERA and a negative platoon variance tipped the scales in favor of **Nolan Schanuel** (60.35) and **Andy Pages** (59.16), whose matchups against higher-xERA pitchers offered better run-production probability. We must remain cautious with **Gunnar Henderson** (56.30), whose score is suppressed by a tough battle against Max Fried; while his elite talent is undeniable, the dynamic platoon disadvantage against a left-handed ace is a situational risk that limits his ceiling for today\u2019s slate. As we await official lineup postings, users should monitor for any late-breaking shifts that could further impact the viability of our current bench depth, including potential spot starts for **Coby Mayo** or **Brady House** if order positions fluctuate.",
